description:
Bug 38131ajc needs -d. I am using version 1.1rc1. This is a regression since rc1 and a deviation from javac. I am guessing this may have something to do with a change in the underlying Eclipse compiler.

To reproduce the issue:
1. Create a class in a subpackage such as:

package subpackage;

public class Test {
    public static void main(String[] args) {
        System.out.println("Hello");
    }
}

2. Compile using the following command: ajc subpackage\Test.java

Observed Behavior:
- A directory named "subpackage" is created under the existing "subpackage" directory.
- The test.class file is put in the subpackage\subpackage directory.
- Running the java command results in the following error:
    Exception in thread "main" java.lang.NoClassDefFoundError: subpackage/Test

Expected Behavior:
- Compiling with ajc should not create an additional "subpackage" directory.

Steps to Reproduce:
1. Compile the class using the following command: ajc -d . subpackage\Test.java

Please note that running the java command should not result in any errors.
